article.description: — Kane Milling scored 24 points as UC Davis beat Long Beach State 88-78 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Milling's 24 lead UC Davis over Long Beach State 88-78
article.linkText: Milling's 24 lead UC Davis over Long Beach State 88-78
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- — Kane Milling scored 24 points as UC Davis beat Long Beach State 88-78 on Saturday night. Milling had five rebounds for the Aggies (19-12, 14-6 Big West). Ty Johnson shot 4 of 13 from the field and 9 for 9 from the line to add 18 points. Elijah Pepper shot 4 of 5 from the field and 7 of 7 from the free-throw line to finish with 17 points. Marcus Tsohonis led the Beach (18-14, 10-10) in scoring, finishing with 21 points, five assists and two steals. Jadon Jones added 13 points and two blocks for Long Beach State. AJ George also recorded 11 points and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
